Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about analyzing memory usage in fork-join parallel programs running on massively parallel computing systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper introduces a tool for analyzing Cilk programs. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper discusses the overhead of the Cilkmem tool. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper is about analyzing memory usage in parallel computing systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper is about designing and analyzing software programs.
